&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5 Staff Nurse - Endoscopy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLEASE NOTE: This is a fixed-term post for 12 months to cover maternity leave.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have exciting opportunities for Band 5 Staff Nurses to join our busy Endoscopy Unit, which has recently expanded its services. We are a busy unit within the Royal Berkshire Hospital which has been recently acknowledged as Good by the CQC.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Unit is a JAG accredited Unit where we currently work a 6 day working week and have the benefit of doing self-rostering with priority requests.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Endoscopy Unit is a friendly team and we welcome applications from anyone who is a good team player and has a willingness to learn and develop new skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a busy, diagnostic and therapeutic unit dealing with out-patients and in-patients and we also support the Bowel Cancer Screening and Bowel Scope Programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates don’t have to have any previous experience in Endoscopy, but previous experience in an acute setting is desirable and experience of working on a ward would also be preferable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We provide all in-house training and a mentor is assigned to support you during this time of learning; external study days are also provided for the specialist skills required for the therapeutic work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in joining a dynamic team who strive to provide excellent patient care and are willing to learn and extend your current skills, then please do get in touch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chiedza Chiweshe (Sister) on 0118 322 7458 or chiedza.chiweshe@royalberkshire.nhs.uk or Clare Gardiner (Lead Nurse) on 0118 322 8819 or clare.gardiner@royalberkshire.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
